  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the recognition rate of such datasets is often very high.",
    "Therefore, to promote the sustainable development of action recognition and improve the richness and complexity of datasets, Kuehne et al. proposed HMDB51.",
    "The HMDB51 dataset is a small and easy-to-use human movement dataset, containing 51 action categories and a total of 6849 clips including manual annotation.",
    "There are five action categories: general facial action, facial action and object action, general body action, human interaction, and human action.",
    "Videos were obtained from a variety of sources, from digitized movies to YouTube (Fig. 7)."
